  "prompt": "How can I remove the montage sound from video?",
  "response": "To remove the montage sound from a video, you can use video editing software. Here's a step-by-step guide on how to do it using a popular free tool called Shotcut:\n\n1. **Download and Install Shotcut:**\n   - Go to the Shotcut website and download the software for your operating system.\n   - Install it following the on-screen instructions.\n\n2. **Import Your Video:**\n   - Open Shotcut and click on the `Open File` button to import your video file.\n\n3. **Add the Video to the Timeline:**\n   - Drag the video from the playlist to the timeline at the bottom of the screen.\n\n4. **Remove the Audio:**\n   - Right-click on the video clip in the timeline.\n   - Select `Split Audio`. This will separate the audio from the video into two tracks.\n   - Click on the audio track and press the `Delete` key on your keyboard to remove it.\n\n5. **Export the Video:**\n   - Go to the `File` menu and select `Export`.\n   - Choose your desired format and settings.\n   - Click `Export File` to save the video without the montage sound.\n\nIf you prefer to use a different tool or need a more advanced solution, you can consider using Adobe Premiere Pro, Final Cut Pro, or DaVinci Resolve. The steps will be similar but the interface and specific commands may differ.\n\nHere is a simple Python script using `moviepy` to remove the audio from a video file:\n\n```python\nfrom moviepy.editor import VideoFileClip\n\ndef remove_audio(input_path, output_path):\n    \"\"\"\n    Remove the audio from a video file.\n\n    Args:\n    input_path (str): The path to the input video file.\n    output_path (str): The path to save the output video file without audio.\n    \"\"\"\n    # Load the video clip\n    video_clip = VideoFileClip(input_path)\n    \n    # Remove the audio\n    video_without_audio = video_clip.without_audio()\n    \n    # Write the result to a new file\n    video_without_audio.write_videofile(output_path, codec=\"libx264\", audio_codec=\"None\")\n    \n    # Close the video clip\n    video_clip.close()\n\n# Example usage\ninput_video = \"path/to/your/input_video.mp4\"\noutput_video = \"path/to/your/output_video.mp4\"\nremove_audio(input_video, output_video)\n```\n\nTo use this script, you'll need to install the `moviepy` library:\n\n```bash\npip install moviepy\n```\n\nMake sure to replace `\"path/to/your/input_video.mp4\"` and `\"path/to/your/output_video.mp4\"` with the actual paths to your input and output video files.",
